notesStmt.note: Title from caption (f. 1v); alternate title from introduction (f. 2r).

msContents.summary: An illustrated translation into Persian of a collection of stories of the patriarchs and prophets from the creation to the time of Muḥammad. This collection begins by saying the translation was requested by the (fictitious) Sulṭān Ghiyāth al-Dīn Muẓaffar Khān.

respStmt.persName: Kātib, Malik Muḥammad ibn Darvīsh Muḥammad, active 1574
كاتب، ملك محمد بن درويش محمد،

supportDesc.extent: iii, 228, ii leaves : 310 x 203 (230 x 120) mm, bound to 320 x 210 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Textblock border-ruled in narrow gold, wide gold and blue; rubrications in red; illuminated headpiece in gold, blue, red (f. 1v), 30 color illustrations (f. 7v, 11r, 19r, 22r, 28r, 31v, 36r, 48v, 50v, 52v, 63v, 70r, 75r, 79v, 85v, 90v, 104v, 112v, 114v, 127v, 133r, 139v, 154r, 162r, 167r, 182v, 190v, 198r, 206v, 210r), and an illuminated foliate finispiece in gold (f. 228r).

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard with marbled paper pastedowns.

origin.p: Copy completed in 982 AH by Malik Muḥammad ibn Darvīsh Muḥammad al-Kātib (228r).

history.provenance: Purchased for Columbia with funds donated by J. Dyneley Prince, James Speyer and Jacob H. Schiff; accessioned 1905 (bookplate inside front cover).
Formerly owned by Carl Reinhardt; purchased from his estate.

keywords.term: Illumination of books and manuscripts, Iranian--Specimens
